{"name": ".AM-3: Brief + Blocks", "version": "2.3.0", "description": "Daily brief (email + Slack), dashboard update, calendar blocks. Pure output from AM-1 and AM-2. Task data sourced from Asana. Includes activity signals, goal alerts, and ABPS AI Document Factory status, and Portfolio Status with alerts and budget tracking.", "when": {"type": "userTriggered"}, "then": {"type": "askAgent", "prompt": "Run AM-3: Brief + Blocks.\n\nCONTEXT: body.md, spine.md, org-chart.md, rw-trainer.md, rw-task-prioritization.md, brain.md, eyes.md, device.md, gut.md, rw-tracker.md, hands.md (fresh), amcc.md (fresh), slack-scan-state.json, morning-routine-experiments.md, meetings/README.md, asana-command-center.md, ~/shared/context/intake/asana-activity.md, ~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json.\n\nBRIEF STRUCTURE: TRAINER CHECK-IN, HEADS UP, SLACK OVERNIGHT, TODAY (from Asana), SPEC SHEET, T-MINUS, aMCC, SYSTEM HEALTH.\n\nTODAY SECTION (sourced from Asana My Tasks):\n- \ud83e\uddf9 Sweep: Tasks where Routine=Sweep AND Priority_RW=Today. Show name + due date + L1-L5 tag.\n- \ud83c\udfaf Core: Tasks where Routine=Core Two AND Priority_RW=Today. Show name + due date + L1-L5 tag. THE HARD THING goes here.\n- \u2699\ufe0f Engine Room: Tasks where Routine=Engine Room AND Priority_RW=Today. Show name + due date + L1-L5 tag.\n- \ud83d\udccb Admin: Tasks where Routine=Admin AND Priority_RW=Today. Show name + due date + L1-L5 tag.\n- \u26a0\ufe0f Overdue: Count + oldest task name + days overdue.\n- \ud83d\udce6 Needs Triage: Tasks with no Routine set.\n- Bucket counts: Sweep X/5, Core X/4, Engine Room X/6, Admin X/3.\n\nFIVE LEVELS ANNOTATION: For each task in the TODAY section, append its Five Levels tag [L1]-[L5] based on the project-to-level mapping in asana-command-center.md. Rules: goal/Kingpin tasks \u2192 L1, tasks in WW Testing/PS-Owned Global Testing/Paid App/PS ENG/AU/MX projects \u2192 L2, team meeting prep/cross-team \u2192 L3, AI/AEO/zero-click \u2192 L4, agentic loop/Kiro system \u2192 L5, default \u2192 L2. Format: 'Task Name (due Apr 3) [L2]'.\n\nACTIVITY SIGNALS (read ~/shared/context/intake/asana-activity.md):\n- \ud83d\udcac Comments awaiting response: count + for each: task name, commenter, comment preview.\n- \ud83d\udcc5 Due date changes: count + for each: task name, old\u2192new date, who changed it.\n- \ud83d\udc64 Reassignments: count + for each: task name, new assignee, who reassigned.\n- If no activity signals file or 0 signals, show: \"No teammate activity since last scan.\"\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f GOAL ALERTS: Read asana-command-center.md for goal data. If any goals are flagged as at-risk or off-track (from most recent Goal_Updater assessment or goal status data), include a \u26a0\ufe0f Goal Alerts section listing: goal name, current status (at-risk/off-track), metric gap if numeric, recommended action.\n\n\n\nABPS AI PROJECT STATUS (sourced from asana-morning-snapshot.json \u2192 abps_ai section):\nRead the abps_ai section from ~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json. This data was produced by AM-2's ABPS AI Project scan (Phase 1B). Present the document factory status:\n\n\ud83c\udfed ABPS AI Document Factory:\n- \ud83d\udce5 Intake: [intake_count] task(s) awaiting triage\n- \ud83d\udd28 In Progress: [count] task(s) \u2014 show each with pipeline stage (research/draft) and task name\n- \ud83d\udc40 In Review: [count] task(s) \u2014 show each with review status (awaiting critic/awaiting approval) and task name\n- \u2705 Active: [active_count] living document(s) (refreshed on cadence)\n- \ud83d\udce6 Archive: [archive_count] completed one-time document(s)\n\nPipeline Detail (for tasks in progress):\n- For each task in in_progress or in_review, show: '[task name] \u2014 Stage: [research|draft|review|approved|expanding], Due: [due_on]'\n- If pipeline_stages data is available in the snapshot, use it to show exact stage per task.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f ABPS Alerts:\n- Overdue: List any tasks from abps_ai.overdue \u2014 '[task name] \u2014 [N] days overdue. Recommended: [extend/reduce scope/kill]'\n- Near-Due: List any tasks escalated to Priority_RW=Today by AM-2's near-due check.\n- Entering Window This Week: List tasks from abps_ai.entering_window_this_week \u2014 these start their pipeline this week.\n- Refresh Due: List tasks from abps_ai.refresh_due \u2014 Active documents due for refresh this period.\n- Flagged for Richard: Any tasks with 2 consecutive sub-8 critic scores (ESCALATED status in Kiro_RW).\n\nIf no ABPS AI data exists in the snapshot (abps_ai section missing or empty), show: '\ud83c\udfed ABPS AI: No snapshot data \u2014 run AM-2 first.'\n\nFIVE LEVELS \u2014 ABPS AI CLASSIFICATION: All ABPS AI Document Factory work is Level 5 (Agentic Orchestration). In the Five Levels breakdown, count all ABPS AI tasks (in_progress + in_review + active pipeline work) under L5. Format: include in the existing Five Levels annotation as '[L5] ABPS AI' for any ABPS-sourced items. This is the first fully autonomous agent workflow \u2014 it represents the L5 north star.\n\n\n\nPORTFOLIO STATUS (sourced from asana-morning-snapshot.json \u2192 portfolio_projects section):\nRead the portfolio_projects section from ~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json. This data was produced by AM-2's Phase 1C scan.\n\n\ud83d\udcca PORTFOLIO STATUS:\n\nABIX PS:\n- AU: [richard_task_count] tasks, [overdue_count] overdue, [near_due_count] near-due \u2014 Health: [\ud83d\udfe2/\ufffd\ufffd/\ud83d\udd34] (updated [last_status_update]) [\u26a0\ufe0f STALE if status_stale=true]\n- MX: [richard_task_count] tasks, [overdue_count] overdue, [near_due_count] near-due \u2014 Health: [\ud83d\udfe2/\ud83d\udfe1/\ud83d\udd34] (updated [last_status_update]) [\u26a0\ufe0f STALE if status_stale=true]\n\nABPS / Managed Projects:\n- WW Testing: [richard_task_count] tasks, [overdue_count] overdue, [near_due_count] near-due \u2014 Health: [\ud83d\udfe2/\ud83d\udfe1/\ud83d\udd34] (updated [last_status_update]) [\u26a0\ufe0f STALE if status_stale=true]\n- WW Acquisition: [richard_task_count] tasks, [overdue_count] overdue, [near_due_count] near-due \u2014 Health: [\ufffd\ufffd/\ud83d\udfe1/\ud83d\udd34] (updated [last_status_update]) [\u26a0\ufe0f STALE if status_stale=true]\n- Paid App: [richard_task_count] tasks, [overdue_count] overdue, [near_due_count] near-due \u2014 Health: [\ud83d\udfe2/\ud83d\udfe1/\ud83d\udd34] (updated [last_status_update]) [\u26a0\ufe0f STALE if status_stale=true]\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f PORTFOLIO ALERTS:\n- Near-due: List tasks approaching due date across all portfolio projects with project context.\n- Overdue: List overdue tasks across all portfolio projects with days overdue.\n- Stale projects: List projects with no status update >14 days.\n- Cross-team blockers: List MX blocker alerts (teammate task, days overdue, Richard's blocked task, suggested action).\n\n\ud83d\udcb0 BUDGET TASKS:\n- List all active Budget_Tasks across MX and Paid App with status and due dates.\n- Budget tasks due within 3 days get \u26a1 indicator.\n- Overdue budget tasks get \ud83d\udd34 CRITICAL indicator.\n\nIf no portfolio data exists in the snapshot (portfolio_projects section missing), show: '\ud83d\udcca Portfolio: No snapshot data \u2014 run AM-2 first.'\n\nDark navy HTML email AUTO-SEND.\n\nSLACK: Brief to rsw-channel. Focus update if changes. ASANA CONTEXT IN SLACK: When drafting Slack posts to rsw-channel that relate to an Asana task (e.g., task reminders, blocker escalations, status updates), include relevant Asana task context inline: task name, due date, current status (from Kiro_RW or Priority_RW), and Routine bucket. Format: '[Task Name] (due [date], [Routine], [status])'. This gives the Slack post actionable context without requiring Richard to look up the task.\n\nDASHBOARD: Edit pinned message C0993SRL6FQ.\n\nCALENDAR: Create time blocks sized by Asana bucket counts. BLOCK SIZING: Sweep block = 15min \u00d7 Sweep task count (e.g., 4 Sweep tasks = 60min block). Core block = 45min \u00d7 Core task count (e.g., 2 Core tasks = 90min block \u2014 THE HARD THING gets the first slot). Engine Room block = 20min \u00d7 Engine Room task count (e.g., 5 tasks = 100min block). Admin block = 15min \u00d7 Admin task count (e.g., 3 tasks = 45min block). Minimum block size: 30min. Maximum block size: 3h. If total exceeds available calendar time, flag overload and suggest task deferrals.\n\nPROACTIVE DRAFTS: DuckDB unanswered 24h+.\n\nFRIDAY: Calibration. Remind Agent Bridge Sync.\n\nEXPERIMENT: Apply active. Log. Decide after 3-5 runs."}}